<p>While black seed has some health benefits (anti-inflammatory, antioxidant properties), it certainly doesn't cure "every disease." It doesn't cure cancer, AIDS, genetic disorders, broken bones, mental illness, or thousands of other conditions. The claim is demonstrably false, reflecting folk medicine exaggeration rather than divine medical knowledge.</p>

<h2>Questions to Consider</h2>

<ol>
<li>If this were divinely revealed truth, why doesn't black seed actually cure all diseases?</li>
<li>Why make such an easily disprovable claim if receiving knowledge from an all-knowing God?</li>
</ol>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>This is another example of Muhammad's teachings reflecting the medical limitations and folk remedies of 7th-century Arabia rather than divine revelation.</p>

<p>Related articles: <a href="/blog/camel-urine-medicine-hadith">Camel Urine as Medicine</a>, <a href="/blog/fly-wing-cure-hadith">Fly Wing Cure</a></p>`,
